    <text id="R1514012T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Adjutant C. L. Stevenson writes Colonel William B. Taliaferro
                    concerning November, 1861, orders. Stevenson mentions that General William
                    Loring went to Staunton to discuss troop movements.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    ADJUTANT-GEN.'S OFFICE, ARMY OF NORTHWEST
                    <name type="recipient">Col. W. B. TALIAFERRO,<lb/> Cmdg., &amp;c., at or
                        near Ryan's, Monterey Line:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-11-30">November 30, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">Huntersville, Va.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>COL.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter of the 29th, inclosing the telegram from Gen. Cooper of the 28th, I
                    have just received. A letter from the Secretary of War, dated 24th instant, with
                    regard to a movement of the troops of this army, was received by Gen. Loring two
                    days since, and he left here on yesterday for Staunton on business connected
                    therewith. I respectfully suggest that you wait at Ryan's further orders from
                    him. The information forwarded to you will be dispatched to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</salute>
                    <signed>C. L. STEVENSON,<lb/> Adjutant-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
